<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="177" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72111/1396½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1915</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I enclose a
                                statement<note n="29" xml:id="d177fn1">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> which, with your approval, I
                            will give out to the press, in regard to the demands made upon us to
                            protest against the invasion of Belgium by Germany. Mr. Lansing prepared
                            a memorandum to which I made some amendments and this statement is the
                            result of our conference on the subject. If you will return Mr.
                            Lansing’s letter and this statement with such corrections as you wish to
                            make, I will give the statement out early next week.</p>
                        <p>With assurances [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>